    From ST0903:

    The velocity of the entity at the time of last detection.

      • Velocity

        public Velocity(byte[] bytes,
                EncodingMode encodingMode)
        Create from encoded bytes.

        ST0903 changed the encoding for each element to 2-byte IMAPB in ST0903.4. Earlier versions used a two-byte unsigned integer structure in the range [0, 2^16-1]that was then mapped into the same ranges that the IMAPB encoding uses. Which formatting applies can only be determined from the ST0903 version in the parent VmtiLocalSet. The compatibilityMode parameter determines whether to parse using the legacy encoding or current encoding.

        Note that this only affects parsing. Output encoding is always IMAPB (ST0903.4 or later).

        Parameters:
        bytes - The byte array of length 6, 12 or 18.
        encodingMode - which encoding mode the bytes parameter uses
